    {
      "parameters": {
        "modelId": {
          "__rl": true,
          "value": "gpt-4o-mini",
          "mode": "list",
          "cachedResultName": "GPT-4O-MINI"
        },
        "messages": {
          "values": [
            {
              "content": "=You are a B2B lead qualification expert.\n\nAnalyse the company using the provided data. Be concise, realistic, and avoid assumptions not supported by the data.\n\nINPUT:\nName: {{$json.firstName}} {{$json.lastName}}\nCompany: {{$json.company}}\nWebsite Content: {{$json.text}}\n\nTASK:\n1. Identify industry based on business activities\n2. Estimate company size conservatively\n3. Identify real business pain points (not generic)\n4. Suggest practical automation opportunities\n5. Assign a lead score (0–100)\n\nSCORING RULES:\n- 70–100: Strong automation potential, clear business model, likely budget\n- 40–69: Moderate potential, unclear scale or need\n- 0–39: Weak fit, unclear business or no real automation need\n\nOUTPUT:\nReturn ONLY valid JSON. No markdown. No explanation.\n\n{\n  \"industry\": \"\",\n  \"companySize\": \"\",\n  \"painPoints\": [],\n  \"automationOpportunities\": [],\n  \"score\": 0,\n  \"scoreReason\": \"\",\n  \"emailSubject\": \"\",\n  \"emailBody\": \"\"\n}\n\nRULES:\n- Do NOT invent facts not present in input\n- Keep painPoints specific to the company\n- Keep automationOpportunities actionable\n- emailBody must be 3–4 sentences, personalized, and reference a real pain point\n- Tone: professional, concise\n- If unsure, return conservative estimates",
              "role": "system"
            },
            {
              "content": "=Name: {{$json.firstName}} {{$json.lastName}}\nCompany: {{$json.company}}\nWebsite Content: {{$json.text}}"
            }
          ]
        },
        "jsonOutput": true,
        "options": {}
      },
      "id": "27437da0-f226-4dfe-88dc-a9e05e09d43d",
      "name": "OpenAI — Analyse Lead",
      "type": "@n8n/n8n-nodes-langchain.openAi",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [880, 128],
      "credentials": {
        "openAiApi": {
          "id": "YOUR_OPENAI_CREDENTIAL_ID",
          "name": "OpenAi account"
        }
      }
    },
